 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-SOUND-2: F(S) fitness function is NOT monotonic -- INV-BILATERAL-001 L1 is FALSE [CRITICAL]. The spec claims F(S(t+1)) >= F(S(t)). Code analysis proves this false via 4 mechanisms: (1) Adding unwitnessed spec element lowers V (validation=witnessed/total_specs) and C (coverage). (2) Adding low-confidence exploration lowers U (uncertainty complement=mean confidence). (3) Task close flow in task.rs:1176 measures actual_delta that empirically goes negative. (4) MaterializedViews vs batch F(S) produce different values for identical store state. The Lyapunov analysis at bilateral.rs:1875 reports violations without enforcing. SOLUTION: Two options: (A) High-water-mark approach: F(S) = max(current, previous). Preserves convergence guarantee but may mislead about current state. (B) Accept non-monotonicity, revise INV-BILATERAL-001 to remove L1 claim, reframe F(S) as informational snapshot not Lyapunov function. Option B is more honest. JUSTIFICATION: A non-monotonic fitness function cannot serve as Lyapunov function for convergence analysis. The guidance system assumes F(S) indicates progress; if valid work decreases F(S), system punishes correct behavior. VERIFICATION: Proptest: generate random valid operations, measure F(S) before/after, document which decrease it. DEPENDENCIES: Interacts with AUDIT-SOUND-3 (hypothesis mismatch). Interacts with AUDIT-LOOP-1 (calibration). Risk: if redesigned, all historical F(S) values in store become stale."
